All subjects were male, recruited from different provinces, such as Guangdong, Guangxi, Hubei, Liaoning, Shandong. The mean age of subjects was 18.07 ± 1.05 years (range 18–23 years). The differences of age, educational level and other demographic characteristics were not statistical significance between two groups (Table 1
). Compliance rates between two groups were not statistically significant different, which the experimental group was 99.03% and the control group was 98.35% (p
 = 0.257).
